Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: pyfuncrun
Version: 0.1.4.1
Summary: A tool to run a python function in a module from command line
Home-page: https://github.com/zhangliyong/pyfuncrun
Author: Lyon Zhang
Author-email: lyzhang87@gmail.com
License: BSD
Description: pyfuncrun
        =========
        
        Run a python function in a module from command line
        
        Install
        ---------
        
        .. code-block:: bash
        
            $ pip install pyfuncrun
        
        Usage
        -----
        
        .. code-block:: bash
        
            $ pyfuncrun <path.to.func> <func arguments> <arguments for func to parse in sys.argv>
        
        
        Example
        -------
        
        func.py:
        
        .. code-block:: python
        
            def print_sys_argv():
                print sys.argv
        
        
            def func_with_args(a, b):
                print ((a + b), sys.argv)
        
        
            def func_with_kwargs(a, b, c=1):
                print ((a + b + c), sys.argv)
        
        Run:
        
        .. code-block:: bash
        
            $ pyfuncrun func.print_sys_argv 1 2
            ['pyfuncrun', 1, 2]
        
            $ pyfuncrun func.func_with_args 1 2
            (3, ['pyfuncrun'])
        
            $ pyfuncrun func.func_with_kwargs 1 2 3 4
            (6, ['pyfuncrun', 4])
        
Platform: UNKNOWN
